he traversal.\n\nReturn an array of integers `result` containing, **in order**, the value of the cells visited during the zigzag traversal with skips.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** grid = [[1,2],[3,4]]\n\n**Output:** [1,4]\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3417-zigzag-grid-traversal-with-skip/3417-4012_example0.png","sequence":1,"sha256":"2403a9ae4fed79aa6449a9524b21d051d8dada7ee6702f2665f7ebd4d4d32b76","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** grid = [[2,1],[2,1],[2,1]]\n\n**Output:** [2,1,2]\n\n**Explanation:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3417-zigzag-grid-traversal-with-skip/3417-4012_example1.png","sequence":3,"sha256":"3b0a09fa3733f568670a60d25e49dca9b0075aa4333818d9eda8cddf3e1c255f","type":"image"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**\n\n**Input:** grid = [[1,2,3],[4,5,6],[7,8,9]]\n\n**Output:** [1,3,5,7,9]\n\n**Explanation:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3417-zigzag-grid-traversal-with-skip/3417-4012_example2.png","sequence":5,"sha256":"b7b8481afc4ddc3bddb9af14e168f2cdef67831de10152fcc652f53720e6634d","type":"image"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `2 <= n == grid.length <= 50`\n\n- `2 <= m == grid[i].length <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= grid[i][j] <= 2500`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Easy","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given an `m x n` 2D array `grid` of **positive** integers.\n\nYour task is to traverse `grid` in a **zigzag** pattern while skipping every **alternate** cell.\n\nZigzag pattern traversal is defined as following the below actions:\n\n- Start at the top-left cell `(0, 0)`.\n\n- Move *right* within a row until the end of the row is reached.\n\n- Drop down to the next row, then traverse *left* until the beginning of the row is reached.\n\n